Spring MVC – 
  Spring MVC is a Java-based web framework built on top of the Spring Framework following the Model-View-Controller (MVC) design pattern.
Core Architecture :
    Client sends HTTP request
    DispatcherServlet (Front Controller) receives it
    It checks HandlerMapping → finds controller method
    HandlerAdapter invokes the controller
    Controller returns:
    View name OR
    Response body (JSON/XML)
    ViewResolver resolves view (JSP/Thymeleaf)
    Response returned to client

Internal Working:
  Example Request: /users
  DispatcherServlet receives request
  Calls HandlerMapping → finds UserController#getUsers()
  HandlerAdapter invokes method
  Controller returns "users"
  ViewResolver → /WEB-INF/views/users.jsp
  View renders response
  
 Key Components :
 1. DispatcherServlet:
      Central controller of Spring MVC
      Handles all incoming requests
      Defined in web.xml (older) or auto-configured in Spring Boot
      Think of it as:“Traffic police of all requests”
 2. HandlerMapping:
      Maps URL → Controller method
      Example:
      @RequestMapping("/users")
3. HandlerAdapter:
      Executes the mapped controller method
      Allows different controller types
4. Controller:
      Business logic layer
      @Controller
      public class UserController {
          @GetMapping("/user")
          public String getUser(Model model) {
              model.addAttribute("name", "John");
              return "user";
          }
      }
5. Model:
      Holds data to be sent to view
6. ViewResolver:
      Resolves logical view name → actual file
      prefix=/WEB-INF/views/
      suffix=.jsp
7. View:
      UI layer (JSP, Thymeleaf, etc.)
      
MVC Pattern Explained:
      Component	    Responsibility
      Model	        Data
      View	        UI
      Controller	  Handles request & response
      
Important Annotations:
🔹 Core:
      @Controller → Marks controller
      @RestController → Controller + JSON response
      @RequestMapping → URL mapping
🔹 HTTP Methods:
      @GetMapping
      @PostMapping
      @PutMapping
      @DeleteMapping
🔹 Data Binding:
      @RequestParam - comes in the url "?sortBy=Desc"
      @PathVariable - comes in the ur "/{userId}"
      @RequestBody
      @ModelAttribute
🔹 Example:
    @GetMapping("/user/{id}")
    public String getUser(@PathVariable int id) {
        return "user";
    }
    
Data Binding & Validation:
    Binding Request → Object
    @PostMapping("/save")
    public String save(@ModelAttribute User user) {
    }
Validation:
    @Valid User user
    BindingResult result
    
