Performance Tips:
    Use @RestController for APIs
    Avoid heavy logic in controllers
    Use caching
    Use async processing   

 1. Why DispatcherServlet is needed?-> Centralized request handling → decouples components
 2. Difference: @Controller vs @RestController
          @Controller	          @RestController
          Returns View	        Returns JSON
          Needs @ResponseBody	  Built-in
3. @RequestParam vs @PathVariable
      Feature	    RequestParam	  PathVariable
      URL	        /user?id=1	    /user/1
      Optional	  Yes	            No
4. What happens if no ViewResolver? You’ll get: HTTP 404 / View not found
5. Can multiple HandlerMappings exist?  YES ✔️ (Spring checks in order)
6. Is Spring MVC thread-safe? -> Controllers are singleton. Must avoid shared mutable state
7. Difference: Forward vs Redirect
      Forward      	Redirect
      Server-side	  Client-side
      Same request	New request
8. How JSON conversion happens? Via:HttpMessageConverter. Uses Jackson internally
9. What is ModelAndView? - return new ModelAndView("view", "data", obj);
10. Can we skip DispatcherServlet? ❌ NO — core of Spring MVC

